column348:
Divine. Mesmerizing.
Forget everything, just get lost there and appreciate what mother nature has for us.
It's a treck of around 45-60 mins (about 2.5-3 kms, but quite steep and lot of steps as well). Most of the way is muddy and gets slippery, so get your shoes accordingly, saw many people struggling with it. There are no food joints on the way, not even water, so get it before starting from a small food joint at the starting. You will want to enjoy the beauty at the top, at least worth couple of hours, so starting around 1-2 would be the ideal time, as before that it gets pretty hot and humid. People also camp at the night on the top, in case you're interested.
Now, talking about the place, it's simply amazing. The views are mesmerizing and the whistling wind and chirpings just add to it. In your way to the top, you'll find many beautiful spots, so just sit, relax, switch off your phones and soak the beauty.
This place is an escape and somehow managed to be hidden, and i just hope it stays like this.

I tried out three hotels and I must say, the government tourist lodge in chaltlang is one of the better ones.
It will mean staying 8 mins away by taxi from  the city. But you will get a large room for a couple. Hot water from the geyser will be available in the shower, bath and sink area. A taxi from here to the city will amountnto 150 rs. The stay is much more peaceful. The room price is very affordable and so is the food off the menu.

The booking now can only be done online. The booking from the front desk does not exist anymore.

1 room for a couple will cost 1000 and a room for a single person will come to 800.

There is set times to order breakfast , lunch and dinner.
Room service is available. Drinking water is available from RO filters available  in the corridor outside your room.

column326:
Situated in the middle of Lake Rudrasagar, Neermahal is one of the largest Lake Palace of India. It is around 55kms from the capital city Agartala.
Built in 1930, this was the Summer Palace for the King and his family
The palace is a treat to the eyes of visitors. It has got 24 rooms, a spacious terrace which can be accessed though spiral starcases, beautiful lawn and an amazing garden. The view of the lake from the terrace is breathtaking.
The picturesque Palace is a heaven for photo enthusiasts.
One can reach there by ferry/boat which charges Rs 50 per person and there is an entry fee of Rs 30 for the palace.
Helpful tips
1. Palace opens at 9:30. Early visit is recommended to avoid crowds
2. Avoid public holidays and weekends.

column326:
Located near the road in the sidewalk, this seeming random place where hundreds of people walk everyday is quite special. Only those who take their time from their ever busy lives and stop and look to their side can see the beauty that was always there but left unseen.

Here you will be amazed to see hundreds of buildings, valleys and mountains as far as the eye can see, clouds rolling in the distance, the clear blue sky, how beautiful, gorgeous, big and green aizawl is and appreciate the scenery as so many cars and people are just passing by on the side without stopping, without even looking for once to the beauty that is in their side.
I would recommend going here in the morning or in the night as the hundreds of buildings here light up like the stars in the cosmos, and appreciate it in its full essence, the sounds of the birds and trees engulf you without any noise from cars or people.

If you want to take a great photograph, if you want to look at aizawl from a distance, if you want to look at the huge mountains or blue skies with clouds, if you want to see the full scope of hundreds of buildings in the distance, if you want to take a fresh air and just stop and appreciate for a moment, this viewpoint will give you exactly what you need.

The grass cover area is small and a large slope of it is cover in Speargrass, which for some people can add more to its beauty.
From my view, i will definitely visit it again.

column326: Murlen National Park is a national park located in the Champhai district Mizoram in India. The size of the park area is 200 km2 (77 sq mi). The park is situated about 245 km east of Aizawl, and is close to the Chin Hills. It lies north of Lengteng Wildlife Sanctuary in the same district. It covers an area of approximately 100 km2. The tropical, semi-evergreen and sub montane Forests of Murlen are home to a rich variety of flora and fauna. About 15 species of mammals, 150 species of birds, 35 species of Medicinal plants, 2 species of bamboos, and 4 species of orchids so far have been recorded in this Park. In 2012, 36 people were involved in conservation work of Murlen National Park.
